Attend — AI Health Chatbot
A small full-stack app: a static frontend (landing page + chat widget) and a
Node/Express backend that calls the Claude API on the frontend's behalf, so
your API key never reaches the browser.

Structure
attend-app/
├── server.js          # Express backend — calls the Claude API
├── package.json
├── .env.example        # Copy to .env and add your API key
└── public/
    └── index.html       # Frontend — landing page + chat widget
Setup
Install dependencies:
npm install
Copy the environment file and add your key:
cp .env.example .env
Then open .env and set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY to a key from https://console.anthropic.com/
Start the server:
npm start
Open http://localhost:3000 in your browser.
How it works
The frontend (public/index.html) sends chat messages to POST /api/chat
on your own server.
server.js forwards that conversation to the Claude API along with a
system prompt that keeps responses health-focused, non-diagnostic, and
quick to flag emergencies.
The reply is sent back to the frontend and rendered in the chat widget.
Before using this for real users
This is a starting point, not a compliant medical product. Before any real
deployment, you'd want to add: user authentication, rate limiting, logging/
monitoring, a persistent database instead of in-memory chat history, a legal
review of health-data handling (e.g. HIPAA in the US), and a human escalation
path. The current system prompt is a reasonable baseline but should be
reviewed by clinicians before this reaches real patients.
